This checklist provides specific, actionable tips to help college students in India recognize and avoid online threats.

- Use strong, unique passwords for each account(mixed letters, special characters, numbers).

- Install apps only from trusted stores like play store or app store.

- Don't click on suspicious links in emails, whatsapp or any other various social media platforms.

- Keep profiles private and limit personal info(college, address, phone).

- Verify internship or job offers in the official company websites before applying for it.

UPI and financial safety

- Never approve unknown UPI collect requests-you should only enter UPI pin to send money not to receive it.

- Double-check the UPI ID/name before transferring money, especially on OLX, Instagram shops, or Telegram deals.

- Cyber Crime Portal: cybercrime.gov.in

- Cyber Crime Helpline: 1930
